<p>As you can see the internal state of the order is still displayed in the base currency.</p>

<p>When creating the payment, if the order was created with a specific currency, the payment method will have to translate the amount.</p>

<p>
<b>Example</b><br>
In your online store you have EUR as base currency and USD as optional currency, a customer from the United States is browsing your store and he is able to see prices in USD thanks to the currency settings.<br>
The customer decides to buy an article from the store, you will use Marketcloud's API to create an order instance setting the currency to <code>USD</code>.<br>
The internal state of the order will keep all values in EUR because it's the base currency, but you are able to display order totals and subtotals in USD.
</p>

<blockquote class="blockquote-warning"><b>Warning</b><br/>Not every payment integration supporting automatic multi currency handling.<a class="link" target="_blank" href="/documentation/guides/integrations/stripe">Stripe</a> does but, for example, with Braintree you would need different merchant accounts and the most common thing to do is to charge the card in your base currency.</blockquote>